templateAssets.content: This agreement is subject to revision without prior notice. Please check with a counselor every semester to obtain current information about possible changes in the agreement. To learn more about the courses and programs offered at Sonoma State University or the General Education and Upper-division requirements for each major please refer to the university catalog at: http://www.sonoma.edu/catalog/

All courses in the major core, major electives and supporting courses must be taken in the traditional grading mode (A-F).All lower division courses articulated with SSU upper division courses will only receive content credit and not upper division credit.
